criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Age 65 or above;

          -  No history of cerebral vascular disease, Parkinson's disease or other neurological
             deficit;

          -  Chinese version of the Mini-Mental State Examination (MMSE-C) (Folstein, Folstein, &
             McHuge, 1975; Chiu, Lee, Chung, & Kwong, 1994) total score of equal or more than 24;

          -  Able to walk independently indoor for at least 10 meters;

          -  Older adults with moderate to high risk of falling, as indicated by the score of less
             than 24 out of 28 in the Tinetti Balance Assessment Tool (Tinetti, 1986).

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Any potential participant who cannot meet the inclusion criteria.
